WEBVTT

00:00.856 --> 00:02.140
<i>Nine years ago,</i>

00:02.306 --> 00:04.723
I witnessed my mother's murder.

00:04.725 --> 00:07.926
I would have been killed, too,
<i>if it hadn't been for Vincent.</i>

00:07.928 --> 00:09.794
<i>I was part of an experimental</i>

00:09.796 --> 00:11.513
<i>special forces group.</i>

00:11.633 --> 00:14.718
<i>Their goal was to create</i>
<i>the perfect super soldier.</i>

00:14.720 --> 00:17.037
<i>They made us stronger,</i>
<i>faster, better.</i>

00:17.039 --> 00:18.938
<i>But something went wrong.</i>

00:18.940 --> 00:21.024
<i>They gave orders</i>
<i>to kill us all.</i>

00:21.026 --> 00:23.727
<i>Somehow, I survived and have</i>
<i>been in hiding ever since.</i>

00:23.729 --> 00:25.645
<i>Until a case</i>
<i>brought me back to him.</i>

00:25.647 --> 00:28.898
<i>But also alerted the group</i>
<i>that experimented on him.</i>

00:28.900 --> 00:31.818
<i>Now we're both in danger.</i>

00:31.820 --> 00:33.420
And our best chance at survival

00:33.422 --> 00:36.089
<i>is if we save each other.</i>

00:40.110 --> 00:43.112
♪ My mind

00:43.114 --> 00:47.083
♪ Is in a state

00:47.085 --> 00:52.455
♪ 'Cause all I seem to do
is tempt my fate ♪

00:54.308 --> 00:57.093
♪ Well, I try

00:57.095 --> 01:01.231
♪ A bigger space

01:01.233 --> 01:06.319
♪ But all the while
I'm crashing at the gate... ♪

01:10.324 --> 01:11.941
What the hell's going on?

01:11.943 --> 01:13.976
You're putting grooves
in the floor.

01:13.978 --> 01:15.161
I need to get some air.

01:15.163 --> 01:17.330
Open a window.

01:18.616 --> 01:20.116
What's got you so amped up?

01:20.118 --> 01:24.254
Oh, you must have
seen Cat.

01:25.623 --> 01:27.841
That's why you came home
so late, isn't it?

01:27.843 --> 01:29.175
You were with her.

01:31.045 --> 01:33.096
For a little bit, yeah.

01:33.098 --> 01:36.433
I know what you're
gonna say, man, but...

01:36.435 --> 01:41.304
JT, she makes me
feel like... like

01:41.306 --> 01:42.472
I have a life again.

01:42.474 --> 01:43.723
Awfully dangerous
for a guy

01:43.725 --> 01:45.275
who's supposed to be dead.

01:46.861 --> 01:49.062
Seriously,
where are you going?

01:49.064 --> 01:51.364
For a walk.

01:51.366 --> 01:53.566
Stick to rooftops
where it's safe.

01:53.568 --> 01:55.618
I'll be back soon.

01:55.620 --> 01:57.487
If you're going out,
I'm coming with.

01:57.489 --> 01:59.572
No, no,
that is a bad idea.

01:59.574 --> 02:01.207
That makes us even.

02:03.928 --> 02:06.863
So that's why you want to ask
that Sara girl out, right?

02:06.865 --> 02:08.798
Delicate stomach?

02:08.800 --> 02:11.167
That "girl" is a woman
who happens to be

02:11.169 --> 02:13.253
the Associate Chair of
the Earth Sciences Department.

02:13.255 --> 02:15.588
And I'm not asking her out
because I live in

02:15.590 --> 02:16.706
an abandoned warehouse

02:16.708 --> 02:18.541
with a complicated
roommate.

02:18.543 --> 02:20.877
You're afraid
she's gonna say no.

02:22.713 --> 02:24.230
Maybe I'm misinterpreting

02:24.232 --> 02:27.183
our eye contact
at department meetings.

02:27.185 --> 02:29.102
I mean, I think
she's staring at me, but...

02:29.104 --> 02:31.938
Please, please don't shoot me.

02:31.940 --> 02:33.857
Nobody's a hero tonight.

02:33.859 --> 02:35.959
Open up the register
and hit the floor.

02:35.961 --> 02:36.943
I-I have a family.

02:36.945 --> 02:38.111
Let's go!

02:38.113 --> 02:39.729
Yeah.

02:39.731 --> 02:40.947
Now!

